td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Amour Class Buffs...</span><hr size=1> Are the Martial Arts Amour Class buffs really worth the points in Matter Creation at higher lvls? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tamiko>Tamiko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 6:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2136.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amour Class Buffs...</span><hr size=1> I like them at lower levels, ie 85 so far.  I would venture to think they would be worth it at higher levels too, especially to help in areas where your armor falls short.  All pieces generally have a weakness.  Some feel the AC buffs are completely useless but I wouldn't go that far. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uviirruss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viirruss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 8:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2136.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amour Class Buffs...</span><hr size=1> I am not speaking from experience, just what I have heard on this site...<br>
The MA armor buffs are great at lower levels but as your nano skills begin to eat up more and more IP, they begin to loose their appeal. The amount of IP needed keep these nano's up to date far outways their protective value. I hear most MA's say that nano skills needed cost too much IP. IP that could be better applied to more important skills. <p><a href=http://www.anarchy-online.com/character/bio/d/1/name/viirruss>Viirruss</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xixxxor>Xixxxor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 8:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2136.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amour Class Buffs...</span><hr size=1> To me, I do not think that those buffs are worth the IP like some of you have said, plus Matter Creation is dark blue to me (Opi MA). Not to mention that if you group with an Engineer or Adventurer your buffs will look worthless compared to theirs and equivalent levels. Maybe up in levels when you have IP like crazy you could opt for some points in MC to maybe cast some Diamond Skin or higher level nano's but 50-100 I would not recommend it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ualectosf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlectoSF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 1:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2136.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amour Class Buffs...</span><hr size=1> The AC line is worth pursuing...BUT (you knew that was coming) not to the exclusion of other nanos. <br>
<br>
Later in life, it will be very nice to have indeed, especially for soloing. Once you're in ql200 armor, it's about your only option, unless your siamese twin is an engi. <br>
<br>
I think it's a mistake to ignore it, but just the same don't obsess over it either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucrimhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crimhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 428<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 6:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2136.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amour Class Buffs...</span><hr size=1> I raised my mat cret up to the point where I use Greater Wooden Skin, but after that I discovered that it was a huge IP sink to try and raise it anymore. Instead of resetting mat cret I just decided to stop at GWS. Once I max out everything else appropriate to my MA then I will start raising mat cret again. It helps at lower lvls, not so much during in mid lvls, and becomes abit more important at higher lvls. Again, it's what you are comfortable with.<br>
<br>
Hawk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uveldrane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veldrane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 9:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2136.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hi</span><hr size=1> as far as the ac buffs go, its kinda like this:<br>
<br>
at newbie levels 1-50 they are ok, but I Pis tight and i would rather spend it someplace else. you get better AC return if you spend your IP in stats and equip higher armor instead of Matter Creation.<br>
<br>
at mid levels 50-150, the IP is very tight (well up to about 130-140 anyways). then you kinda have to streamline and optimize your characters development, and i would completely ignore puting any IP into matter creat.<br>
<br>
at higher levels 150-190, depends what you wanna do, i have all teh skilsl i ever wanted maxxed, already maxxed. so i not only maxxed matter creat but matter metanorphose as well. i can self buff myself into 1k+ extra AC. it helps a lot, especially on your weak points, with the funky ACs like fire, disease, radiation, cold, etc. Basically everyone, or nearly so, has high or decent Melee and projectile, and decent energy / chemical. its keeping up the rest thats tough and thats where these buffs really come in and do a great deal for you.<br>
<br>
at level 190-200 is pretty musch same as 150-190, but even moreso, i would gho for every last possible bit of AC i could, in fact, even first then HP. i used to have full MK2 and Life imps, and came to conlusion it basically sucks ass.<br>
<br>
full MK2 = 1 extra absorbed hit, full imps set = another hit. whats 2 hits ? its much better if you shave off a 100 points of off every single hit you take in the 1st place by having better ACs. this doubles in PvP. taking 400 instead of 500 or 600 instead of 700 points a hit will save your skin much more and adds up far beyopnd those extra few HP much faster then the life clusters and MK2.<br>
<br>
believe it or not, i often end up tanking, and i do it much much much better on 1/2 the HP of other folks in groups i am with. seriously.<br>
